## 5. Coding Standards (C++23)

### 5.1 Naming Conventions

| Type | Style | Example |
|------|-------|---------|
| Class/Struct | PascalCase | `class RenderPipeline` |
| Function | CamelCase | `RenderFrame(int iArg, int& oArg)` |
| Private member | camelCase + `_` prefix | `_impl`, `_frameNumber` |
| Public member | camelCase | `frameNumber` |
| Enum | PascalCase type + PascalCase values | `enum class PassType { Graphics, Compute }` |
| Macro/Constant | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE or k-prefix | `MAX_MESHLET_VERTICES`, `kDefaultBufferSize` |
| Template param | PascalCase | `typename TResult` |
| Concept | PascalCase | `template<Sender S>` |

### 5.2 C++23 Paradigms (Mandatory)

- **Headers**: Traditional `#include` headers (`.h`) + implementation files (`.cpp`). No C++20/23 modules.
- **Ranges**: `std::views::transform/filter/take/zip`, pipe syntax (`|`), projections over raw loops and classic STL algorithms.
- **Error handling**: `std::expected<T, E>`, no exceptions on hot paths. Chain with `.and_then()` / `.transform()` / `.or_else()` — prefer monadic chains over nested `if (result)`.
- **Output**: `std::format` / `std::print` / `std::println` instead of `std::cout` or `printf`.
- **Deducing this**: `this auto&& self` for CRTP replacement and mixins.
- **Containers**: `std::flat_map` / `std::flat_set` for cache-friendly associative containers.
- **Views**: `std::mdspan` for multidimensional GPU buffer views.
- **Iteration**: `std::generator<T>` for lazy sequences.
- **Callables**: `std::move_only_function` over `std::function`.
- **Hints**: `[[assume(expr)]]` on hot paths, `std::unreachable()` for impossible paths.
- **Compile-time**: Aggressive `constexpr` / `consteval`.
- **Enums**: `std::to_underlying` for enum-to-integer, `enum class` only.
- **Threading**: `std::jthread` + `std::stop_token` for cooperative cancellation.
- **Debug**: `std::stacktrace` for debug/telemetry stack capture.

### 5.3 Code Style Rules

- `[[nodiscard]]` on all functions returning `Result<T>`, `std::expected`, `exec::task<>`, `std::generator<>`
- `explicit` on all single-argument and converting constructors
- `= delete` copy, `noexcept` move for resource-owning types
- Pimpl via `std::unique_ptr<Impl>` for ABI stability on public API boundaries
- `alignas(16)` on GPU-shared structs with `static_assert(sizeof(...) == N)`
- Explicit padding `uint32_t _padding[N]` in GPU structs — no implicit padding
- Async interfaces return `exec::task<Result<T>>` or `stdexec::sender auto`
- Prefer `std::span`, `std::string_view`, `std::mdspan` over raw pointers
- Prefer `std::array` over C-style arrays
- All `.h` files start with `#pragma once`

### 5.4 Comment Style (Doxygen)

Format: `/** @brief ... @param ... @return ... @note ... @see ... */` (multi-line block style).
Tags: `@brief`, `@param`, `@return`, `@note`, `@see`, `@tparam`, `@throws`.

### 5.5 Slang Shader Conventions

| Type | Style | Example |
|------|-------|---------|
| Function | camelCase | `evaluateBrdf(float3 N, float3 V)` |
| Struct | PascalCase | `struct MeshletPayload` |
| Constant | kPrefixCamelCase | `static const uint kMaxMeshletVertices = 64;` |
| Entry point | camelCase | `[shader("compute")] void mainCull(...)` |
| Texture/Buffer | camelCase | `Texture2D<float4> gAlbedo` |

- Default workgroup: `[numthreads(8, 8, 1)]` unless domain-specific
- GPU struct must match C++ counterpart: identical field order, types, padding
- Multi-target: every `.slang` compiles to SPIR-V + DXIL + GLSL 4.30 + WGSL in CI
- One `.slang` per logical unit. Shared utilities in `shaders/common/`

### 5.6 Error Code Ranges

> Full table in `specs/error-code-ranges.md`. Read on-demand when adding new error codes.

### 5.7 Git Commit Conventions

- **Format**: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` — subject imperative, lowercase, no period, <=72 chars
- **Types**: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`, `docs`, `style`, `chore`
- **Scope**: module name or phase id — e.g., `feat(rhi): add IDevice factory`, `test(scene): add ECS stress test`
- **Granularity**: one Task = one commit (squash Steps). Gate Check = separate `chore(phase): complete phase-{nn}-{id}` commit
- **Body** (optional): bullet list of key changes; reference Task ID (`T1a.2.3`)
- **No WIP commits** on main branch; use feature branches `phase/{id}/T{id}.X.Y` if needed

