## 9. Common Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Prevention |
|---------|-----------|
| Missing `#pragma once` | All `.h` files must start with `#pragma once` |
| Creating unnecessary .md files | Only when user explicitly asks |
| Repeating checkpoint responses | Do not acknowledge system-injected checkpoint messages |
| Modifying tests blindly | First determine if test expectation or implementation is wrong |
| Debug build for benchmarks | Always use Release builds for performance testing |
| `<unexpected>` header in coca toolchain | Use `<expected>` — coca LLVM 20 has no `<unexpected>` |
| Layering violation (upper includes lower) | Check namespace/include path against §7 namespace map before adding `#include` |
| Subsystem transition/seam behavior undefined | When two subsystems share a parameter range boundary (e.g., MSDF vs bitmap at 8px), always define crossfade/transition behavior explicitly. Never rely on hard threshold switches for user-facing visual output. Run the §4.2.1 checklist before marking plan complete. |
| Pipeline viz out of sync with codebase | When implementing or completing a pass/component, **always update** `demos/pipeline-viz/src/data/pipelineData.ts`: (1) set `implStatus` to `"implemented"` / `"stub"`, (2) add `implPhase`, (3) add `sourceFiles[]`, (4) add `"T0"` to the pass's `tier` array. Also update OverviewPanel `TIER_FLOWS.T0.steps` to include the new pass. This is part of the Definition of Done for every Task. |
| T0 tier not updated after session | At every session end, **review all newly implemented passes** and verify they have `"T0"` in their tier array and appear in `OverviewPanel TIER_FLOWS.T0.steps`. T0 = "what actually runs in the codebase today". |

