## 10. Harness Maintenance

> Harness = constraints + tools + documentation + feedback loops that keep the Agent productive.
> Reference: OpenAI "Harness Engineering" (2026-02), Mitchell Hashimoto.

### 10.1 Pitfall Log (layered storage)

| Layer | Location | Content | Token cost |
|-------|----------|---------|------------|
| **Hot** | `.windsurfrules` §9 (above) | Top 5-10 high-frequency / cross-module pitfalls | Always injected (~10 lines) |
| **Cold** | `.windsurf/pitfalls.md` | Full history: date, module, trigger, root cause, prevention | Agent reads on-demand via `read_file` when entering a related module |

**Promotion rule**: a pitfall moves from Cold to Hot when it recurs 2+ times OR is cross-module.
**Retirement rule**: a Hot pitfall may be removed from §9 when a linter/CI check covers it mechanically.

### 10.2 Agent Error Feedback Loop

After completing each Task, if the Agent encountered repeated errors during implementation:

1. Record root cause + prevention in `.windsurf/pitfalls.md` (Cold layer)
2. If cross-module or high-frequency, also add to §9 (Hot layer)
3. If preventable by a deterministic check, propose a linter rule or CI step to the user

### 10.3 Deterministic Enforcement (roadmap)

These are planned but NOT yet implemented. Agent should propose when the codebase is large enough:

- **Include direction linter**: Layer N may only `#include` Layer 1..N-1
- **Namespace-directory consistency**: `namespace miki::X` only in `include/miki/X/` and `src/miki/X/`
- **GPU struct discipline check**: `alignas(16)` + `static_assert(sizeof)` + explicit padding

